---
import { Plus, Minus } from 'lucide-react';
---

<section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Get answers to common questions about commissioning and pre-commissioning drawings and our CAD services
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Items -->
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What is the difference between commissioning and pre-commissioning?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Pre-commissioning involves system installation verification, startup procedures, and initial testing 
            before full commissioning begins. Commissioning is the comprehensive process of ensuring systems 
            perform according to design intent through functional performance testing and documentation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What building systems require commissioning documentation?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>All major building systems require commissioning including HVAC systems, electrical power distribution, 
            lighting controls, plumbing systems, fire safety systems, and building automation systems.</p>
            <p>The specific requirements depend on building type, size, and local codes, with additional systems 
            like renewable energy and specialty equipment also requiring commissioning documentation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              How do commissioning drawings support LEED certification?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Commissioning documentation is essential for LEED certification, supporting both fundamental 
            commissioning requirements and enhanced commissioning credits. Our drawings provide the necessary 
            verification documentation for up to 25 LEED points across multiple categories.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What testing protocols are included in commissioning documentation?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Our documentation includes functional performance testing, integrated systems testing, seasonal testing 
            protocols, and warranty period verification. Each protocol specifies measurement points, acceptance 
            criteria, and documentation requirements for comprehensive system verification.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              When should commissioning documentation be prepared?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Commissioning planning should begin during the design phase with preliminary documentation. 
            Pre-commissioning drawings are prepared during construction, and final commissioning documentation 
            is completed during system testing and startup.</p>
            <p>Early involvement ensures comprehensive planning and reduces costly changes during construction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              What CAD formats do you provide for commissioning drawings?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            We provide commissioning drawings in multiple CAD formats including AutoCAD (.dwg), Revit (.rvt), 
            and PDF formats. All drawings include layers for different systems and testing points with detailed 
            annotations and specifications for clear implementation guidance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-8">
              Do you provide ongoing support during the commissioning process?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-8 pb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes, we provide comprehensive support throughout the commissioning process including drawing updates, 
            technical clarifications, coordination with commissioning agents, and assistance with testing procedures. 
            Our team remains available for consultation and modifications as needed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center mt-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-cyan-500 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Start Your Commissioning Project?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6">Our commissioning experts are ready to ensure your building systems perform optimally</p>
        <a href="/contact?#contact-form" class="bg-white text-blue-600 font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors duration-300 inline-block">
          Start Your Project
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Add FAQ toggle functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    const faqButtons = document.querySelectorAll('section button');
    
    faqButtons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function(this: HTMLButtonElement) {
        const content = this.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
        const icon = this.querySelector('svg') as SVGSVGElement;
        
        if (content.style.display === 'none' || content.style.display === '') {
          content.style.display = 'block';
          icon.classList.remove('lucide-plus');
          icon.classList.add('lucide-minus');
        } else {
          content.style.display = 'none';
          icon.classList.remove('lucide-minus');
          icon.classList.add('lucide-plus');
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>